      "bookmarkId": "25623485_5_1786-1882",
      "chapterUid": 5,
      "range": "1786-1882",
      "markText": "明斯基的观点可以用这样一句名言总结——“稳定即不稳定”。乍看矛盾的说法实际上包含深意：经济一片繁荣的时候，其实已经埋下了危机的隐患。稳定性会改变行为、政策制定和商业发展机遇，最终带来不稳定性。",
      "totalCount": 299,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=25623485&chapterUid=5&rangeStart=1786&rangeEnd=1882",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/a8132f907186fbbda819c7a?chapterUid=5&rangeStart=1786&rangeEnd=1882"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "25623485_5_657-679",
      "chapterUid": 5,
      "range": "657-679",
      "markText": "任何想让经济活动有规律可循的尝试都是徒劳的。",
      "totalCount": 102,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=25623485&chapterUid=5&rangeStart=657&rangeEnd=679",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/a8132f907186fbbda819c7a?chapterUid=5&rangeStart=657&rangeEnd=679"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "25623485_32_965-1023",
      "chapterUid": 32,
      "range": "965-1023",
      "markText": "他的理由是如果工作岗位的供给量并未增加，仅仅依靠提供职业培训提升贫困人群的“就业能力”，不过是对失业和贫困的再分配。",
      "totalCount": 96,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=25623485&chapterUid=32&rangeStart=965&rangeEnd=1023",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/a8132f907186fbbda819c7a?chapterUid=32&rangeStart=965&rangeEnd=1023"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "25623485_6_1052-1142",
      "chapterUid": 6,
      "range": "1052-1142",
      "markText": "具有讽刺意味的是，主流经济学家所为恰恰相反：金融体系逐渐变得复杂、难以捉摸时，经济学家们却不断简化金融研究方法，降低华尔街金融创新在经济模型中的重要性，这些模型都是来自学术象牙塔。",
      "totalCount": 90,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=25623485&chapterUid=6&rangeStart=1052&rangeEnd=1142",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/a8132f907186fbbda819c7a?chapterUid=6&rangeStart=1052&rangeEnd=1142"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "25623485_8_1553-1722",
      "chapterUid": 8,
      "range": "1553-1722",
      "markText": "明斯基认为，危机来临时，美联储应担任最后贷款人，防止恐慌的个人、公司和银行抛售金融资产，从而导致债务通缩。",
      "totalCount": 90,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=25623485&chapterUid=8&rangeStart=1553&rangeEnd=1722",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/a8132f907186fbbda819c7a?chapterUid=8&rangeStart=1553&rangeEnd=1722"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "25623485_20_1591-1660",
      "chapterUid": 20,
      "range": "1591-1660",
      "markText": "明斯基认为经济稳定的最大威胁是繁荣，因为繁荣会滋生高风险行为，最终引发危机。引发危机的最大危险不是经济由温和转向滞胀，而是由温和转向爆炸。",
      "totalCount": 84,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=25623485&chapterUid=20&rangeStart=1591&rangeEnd=1660",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/a8132f907186fbbda819c7a?chapterUid=20&rangeStart=1591&rangeEnd=1660"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "25623485_31_399-480",
      "chapterUid": 31,
      "range": "399-480",
      "markText": "自由派发动“向贫困宣战”的理念源于新古典主义对贫困根源的定义——正是穷人本身而不是其所处的经济环境导致了贫困的产生。“向贫困宣战”试图改变的是穷人而不是经济体制。",
      "totalCount": 75,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=25623485&chapterUid=31&rangeStart=399&rangeEnd=480",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/a8132f907186fbbda819c7a?chapterUid=31&rangeStart=399&rangeEnd=480"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "25623485_10_398-463",
      "chapterUid": 10,
      "range": "398-463",
      "markText": "在伦敦政治经济学院的演讲上，克鲁格曼解释明斯基之所以没能获得应有的地位，是因为他的离经叛道，拒绝和主流经济学家一样进行正统的假设。",
      "totalCount": 72,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=25623485&chapterUid=10&rangeStart=398&rangeEnd=463",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/a8132f907186fbbda819c7a?chapterUid=10&rangeStart=398&rangeEnd=463"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "25623485_3_1720-1751",
      "chapterUid": 3,
      "range": "1720-1751",
      "markText": "明斯基甚至认为“最后雇主计划”是政府支出的最重要的自动稳定器。",
      "totalCount": 70,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=25623485&chapterUid=3&rangeStart=1720&rangeEnd=1751",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/a8132f907186fbbda819c7a?chapterUid=3&rangeStart=1720&rangeEnd=1751"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "25623485_13_1301-1367",
      "chapterUid": 13,
      "range": "1301-1367",
      "markText": "货币供给的扩张与收缩随着银行家对客户需求的满足而产生顺周期性。当经营形势良好时，企业很容易获得贷款；而当前景暗淡时，银行不愿意放贷。",
      "totalCount": 70,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=25623485&chapterUid=13&rangeStart=1301&rangeEnd=1367",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/a8132f907186fbbda819c7a?chapterUid=13&rangeStart=1301&rangeEnd=1367"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "25623485_14_2860-2915",
      "chapterUid": 14,
      "range": "2860-2915",
      "markText": "公共基础设施的兴建以及通过“最后雇主计划”提供就业（而非福利）能通过增大供给，提高需求，从而降低通货膨胀水平。",
      "totalCount": 68,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=25623485&chapterUid=14&rangeStart=2860&rangeEnd=2915",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/a8132f907186fbbda819c7a?chapterUid=14&rangeStart=2860&rangeEnd=2915"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "25623485_11_5207-5240",
      "chapterUid": 11,
      "range": "5207-5240",
      "markText": "但对他而言，只有实现了全面就业，减少贫富分化才能真正促进金融稳定。",
      "totalCount": 64,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=25623485&chapterUid=11&rangeStart=5207&rangeEnd=5240",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/a8132f907186fbbda819c7a?chapterUid=11&rangeStart=5207&rangeEnd=5240"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "25623485_3_1848-1911",
      "chapterUid": 3,
      "range": "1848-1911",
      "markText": "但与主流凯恩斯主义观点不同的是，他反对政府的大规模投资，因为其不可持续——如果它能达到几乎充分就业，将会因引起通货膨胀而停止。",
      "totalCount": 60,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=25623485&chapterUid=3&rangeStart=1848&rangeEnd=1911",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/a8132f907186fbbda819c7a?chapterUid=3&rangeStart=1848&rangeEnd=1911"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "25623485_6_895-934",
      "chapterUid": 6,
      "range": "895-934",
      "markText": "金融创新最终都会导致金融危机，例如证券化、提升负债比率、债务分层和杠杆收购等。",
      "totalCount": 60,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=25623485&chapterUid=6&rangeStart=895&rangeEnd=934",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/a8132f907186fbbda819c7a?chapterUid=6&rangeStart=895&rangeEnd=934"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "25623485_14_3481-3516",
      "chapterUid": 14,
      "range": "3481-3516",
      "markText": "高就业率对于经济发展具有稳定性，因为能更多地推动消费增长而非投资增长。",
      "totalCount": 60,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=25623485&chapterUid=14&rangeStart=3481&rangeEnd=3516",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/a8132f907186fbbda819c7a?chapterUid=14&rangeStart=3481&rangeEnd=3516"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "25623485_11_4866-4955",
      "chapterUid": 11,
      "range": "4866-4955",
      "markText": "传统凯恩斯主义基于银行存款乘数效应，而明斯基对银行的理解更为深刻，从资产负债表和资产头寸开始，适用于所有的企业、家庭和政府。他坚持认为，每个人都可以创造货币，区别只是接受度不同。",
      "totalCount": 56,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=25623485&chapterUid=11&rangeStart=4866&rangeEnd=4955",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/a8132f907186fbbda819c7a?chapterUid=11&rangeStart=4866&rangeEnd=4955"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "25623485_11_3602-3688",
      "chapterUid": 11,
      "range": "3602-3688",
      "markText": "假定明斯基的理论无误，则经济动态体系里的稳定转瞬即逝，任何试图促进稳定的行为最终只是带来不稳定。但实际战后经济进入相当长的一段稳定期，说明政策发挥了作用，明斯基过于悲观了。",
      "totalCount": 55,
      "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=25623485&chapterUid=11&rangeStart=3602&rangeEnd=3688",
      "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/a8132f907186fbbda819c7a?chapterUid=11&rangeStart=3602&rangeEnd=3688"
    },
    {
      "bookmarkId": "25623485_13_2185-2278",
